## Adding Stacks

Create a subdirectory for each compose stack:

```
{{ blueprint_host_context.host_name }}/
├── whoami/
│   └── docker-compose.yml
├── monitoring/
│   ├── docker-compose.yml
│   └── prometheus.yml
└── README.md              ← this file (generated, safe to edit)
```

Push to trigger automatic deployment via the host's local GitLab Runner.

## Deploy Target

Files in this directory are synced to `{{ blueprint_host_context.repo_context.compose_base_dir }}/` on the host.
Each stack subdirectory becomes a directory under the compose base:

```
{{ blueprint_host_context.repo_context.compose_base_dir }}/
├── whoami/
│   └── docker-compose.yml
└── monitoring/
    ├── docker-compose.yml
    └── prometheus.yml
```

